doc.ContractDescription: THE PROPOSED PROJECT IS TO INVESTIGATE INDUCTIVE-DYNAMIC MAGNETOSPHERE-IONOSPHERE/THERMOSPHERE COUPLING FROM IONOSPHERE-THERMOSPHERE PERSPECTIVES. IT IS TO ADDRESS FUNDAMENTAL SCIENCE QUESTIONS IDENTIFIED IN NASA HELIOPHYSICS ROADMAP AS TO HOW THE MAGNETOSPHERE AND IONOSPHERE-THERMOSPHERE SYSTEMS INTERACT WITH EACH OTHER, WHAT IS RESPONSIBLE FOR THE DRAMATIC VARIABILITY IN MANY OF THE STATE VARIABLES DESCRIBING THE MAGNETOSPHERE-IONOSPHERE-THERMOSPHERE REGION, HOW PLASMAS AND CHARGED PARTICLES ARE HEATED AND ACCELERATED, AND WHAT GOVERNS THE COUPLING OF NEUTRAL AND IONIZED SPECIES. THE FOCUS OF THE INVESTIGATION IS THE DYNAMICS OF THE MAGNETOSPHERE IONOSPHERE/THERMOSPHERE SYSTEM IN THE TRANSIENT STAGE WHEN THE SYSTEM CHANGES FROM ONE STATE TO ANOTHER. THIS TRANSITION, WHICH COVERS A TIME SPAN FROM A FEW MINUTES TO ABOUT HALF AN HOUR, IS OF THE SAME TIME SCALES OF MANY MOST IMPORTANT PHENOMENA IN THE MAGNETOSPHERE AND IONOSPHERE, SUCH AS SUBSTORMS AND AURORAL BRIGHTENING. DURING SUCH TRANSIENT PERIODS (E.G., SUBSTORMS), LARGE AMPLITUDES OF FLUCTUATIONS ARE PRODUCED IN THE STATE VARIABLES AND EXISTING STEADY-STATE MODELS AND DESCRIPTIONS ARE NOT APPLICABLE. OUR STUDIES WILL SIGNIFICANTLY ADVANCE THE UNDERSTANDING OF PHYSICAL PROCESSES DURING THE TRANSIENT PERIOD. ENHANCED HEATING OF THE IONOSPHERE-THERMOSPHERE OCCURS DURING THE TRANSIENT PERIOD AND IONOSPHERE/THERMOSPHERE OUTFLOW MAY BE AMONG ITS DIRECT CONSEQUENCES. OUR STUDIES WILL PROVIDE A BETTER DESCRIPTION OF THE IONOSPHERE/THERMOSPHERE HEATING CAUSED BY THE MAGNETOSPHERIC ENERGY INPUT AND A BETTER UNDERSTANDING OF EFFECTS OF SUCH HEATING ON THE UPFLOW/OUTFLOW OF NEUTRALS AND IONOSPHERIC PLASMA. THE PROPOSED INVESTIGATION TAKES A DIFFERENT APPROACH FROM MOST OF THE CONVENTIONAL MODELS THAT ASSUME THAT THE IONOSPHERE IS EITHER IN QUASI-STEADY STATES OR AS A HEIGHT-INTEGRATED LAYER. THE INVESTIGATION WILL BE BASED ON FIRST-PRINCIPLE EQUATIONS, INCLUDING MAXWELL EQUATIONS, GENERALIZED OHM'S LAW, AND CONTINUITY, MOMENTUM AND ENERGY EQUATIONS FOR ION AND NEUTRAL SPECIES. ALL TIME DERIVATIVES, INCLUDING THE INDUCTIVE EFFECT OF THE ELECTROMAGNETIC FIELD AND BOTH PLASMA AND NEUTRAL DYNAMICS, ARE SELF-CONSISTENTLY TREATED. IN CONTRAST, ALMOST ALL CURRENTLY AVAILABLE MODELS OF THE IONOSPHERE NEGLECT THE INDUCTIVE ELECTRIC FIELD ASSOCIATED WITH THE VARYING MAGNETIC FIELD. IN OUR INVESTIGATION, THE IONOSPHERE/THERMOSPHERE WILL BE TREATED AS A STRUCTURED LAYER INSTEAD OF A HEIGHT-INTEGRATED BOUNDARY OF THE MAGNETOSPHERE. WE WILL TAKE THE METHODOLOGY OF FROM IDEAL TO MORE REALISTIC AND FROM SIMPLE TO MORE COMPLICATED SITUATIONS. IN EACH SUBSEQUENT STEP WE WILL TACKLE THE MOST DOMINANT PROCESSES OR EFFECTS THAT HAVE NOT BEEN TREATED IN THE LAST STEP. WE WILL FIRST CONDUCT ANALYTICAL ANALYSES UNDER VARIOUS SIMPLIFYING GEOMETRIES AND CONDITIONS. AFTER GAINING PHYSICAL UNDERSTANDING OF THE PROCESSES THAT ARE DESCRIBED BY THE GOVERNING EQUATIONS, NUMERICAL MODELS WILL BE DEVELOPED. WE WILL EXTEND OUR ONE-DIMENSIONAL TWO-VELOCITY COMPONENT MODEL FOR A STRATIFIED IONOSPHERE TO MORE GENERAL SITUATIONS. EVENTUALLY A TWO-DIMENSIONAL MODEL WILL BE DEVELOPED TO INVESTIGATE THE COUPLING PROCESSES UNDER MORE REALISTIC CONDITIONS AND GEOMETRIES BY INCLUDING MORE EFFECTS. THE SIGNIFICANCE OF THE PROPOSED RESEARCH IS THAT WE WILL PROVIDE A GREATLY IMPROVED DESCRIPTION OF THE MAGNETOSPHERE-IONOSPHERE/THERMOSPHERE COUPLING IN GENERAL AND OF THE STRONG DYNAMIC VARIATIONS OF THE IONOSPHERE/THERMOSPHERE IN PARTICULAR. THE RESEARCH IS WITHIN THE SCOPE OF GEOSPACE SUPPORTING RESEARCH AND TECHNOLOGY PROGRAM THAT SUPPORTS THEORETICAL RESEARCH, THE DEVELOPMENT AND EXERCISE OF MODELS AND SIMULATIONS, AND THE ANALYSIS AND INTERPRETATION OF DATA FOR THE PURPOSES OF IDENTIFYING AND UNDERSTANDING THE PHYSICAL PROCESSES IMPORTANT TO GEOSPACE STRUCTURE AND DYNAMICS. THE PROPOSAL IS DIRECTLY RELATED TO ORIGIN OF NEAR-EARTH PLASMA (ONEP) SINCE THE IONOSPHERIC PLASMA UPFLOW/OUTFLOW WILL BE INVESTIGATED.
